zes a coarse spatial\ngrid. We find that cloudy phase curves provide much better agreement with the\nWFC3 and Spitzer nightside data, while still closely matching the dayside\nemission. This work provides the community with a convenient, user-friendly\ntool to interpret phase-resolved observations of exoplanet atmospheres using 3D\nmodels.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Apr 2022 16:16:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 17 May 2022 15:43:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-18"}
